						               													<description>As an agent for hire you&amp;rsquo;re tasked with expiring a number of Synthetic beings known to be operating in the City.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;During the game you will visit locations and perform tasks in the optimum order to bring in the most Synthetics before the other agents.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Green, Chems &amp;amp; Steel is played over a number of rounds until one player has expired the majority of the synthetics.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;On your turn you draw 1 location card, plus the number of location bonuses on your player card.  You also collect 1 resource of your choice, plus the number of resource bonuses on your player card.  You then spend resources to complete the locations cards in the order of your choice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Some locations will cause you to deactivate your player bonuses, others will set traps for other players.  Any locations you cannot complete may provide bonuses for the other player(s).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of your turn you discard all resources down to 1 plus any discard bonuses on your player card.  All the completed locations are discarded and the next player takes their turn.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends instantly if a player has expired the majority of synthetics.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
